The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Mobile ban for DU exams

 New Delhi, May 6 (PTI): Delhi University today asked students not to carry communication gadgets to examination halls and said any candidate found possessing such items would be booked for using unfair means in the exams.

 In a release, the universitys registrar said students found with mobile phones, scanners, pagers and the like inside the examination hall would not be allowed to continue with the test. The candidate would also be barred from appearing in the rest of the exams. 




